    {
      "title": "AI System Design Interview Coach",
      "description": "Built an end-to-end AI voice pipeline that simulates real system design interviews, enabling adaptive, low-latency verbal Q&A with a fine-tuned Llama-3 model via LoRA adapters trained on system design corpora. Architected a real-time audio stack Whisper (STT) + Llama-3 LoRA (reasoning/generation) + TTS layer streamed bidirectionally over WebSockets with barge-in handling for natural turn-taking. Implemented context prioritization using cosine similarity scoring against a sliding memory window, managing KV cache growth to keep end-to-end response latency under target thresholds, drawing on MemGPT and Zep architectures. Optimized inference throughput via LoRA adapter quantization and streaming token delivery, reducing time-to-first-token for a responsive, real-time interview experience.",
      "longDescription": "Built an end-to-end AI voice pipeline that simulates real system design interviews, enabling adaptive, low-latency verbal Q&A with a fine-tuned Llama-3 model via LoRA adapters trained on system design corpora. Architected a real-time audio stack Whisper (STT) + Llama-3 LoRA (reasoning/generation) + TTS layer streamed bidirectionally over WebSockets with barge-in handling for natural turn-taking. Implemented context prioritization using cosine similarity scoring against a sliding memory window, managing KV cache growth to keep end-to-end response latency under target thresholds, drawing on MemGPT and Zep architectures. Optimized inference throughput via LoRA adapter quantization and streaming token delivery, reducing time-to-first-token for a responsive, real-time interview experience.",
      "category": "Web Development",
